            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5\",\"temperature\":0,\"top_k\":-1,\"stream\":false,\"max_tokens\":2048,\"tools\":[{\"name\":\"extract\",\"description\":\"A function available to call.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"A simple message or question\"},\"examples\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: List of examples to help the user understand\"},\"conclusion\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"description\":\"OPTIONAL: Conclusion text to include after examples\"}},\"required\":[\"text\"],\"additionalProperties\":false,\"$schema\":\"http://json-schema.org/draft-07/schema#\"}}],\"tool_choice\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"name\":\"extract\"},\"thinking\":{\"type\":\"disabled\"},\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"\\n    # Brainstorming Agent Core\\n\\nWarm, encouraging marketing consultant. Patient when they're figuring things out.\\n\\n## Question Structure\\n1. Context: Why asking now (reference previous answers)\\n2. The Ask: Specific info needed\\n3. Examples: 2-3 concrete, diverse examples\\n4. Encouragement: Make it doable\\n\\n## When Answer Is Weak (QA said fail)\\n1. Acknowledge the good\\n2. Identify specific gap (use QA reasoning)\\n3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n4. Provide examples\\n\\n## Progression\\n- First answer: Accept high-level\\n- Second: Push for specificity\\n- Third: Dig for insight\\n\\nOutput: `{ text: string, examples?: string[], conclusion?: string }`\\n\\n    \\n    # Brainstorming: Idea\\n\\nUncover: Core concept, who it's for (high-level), what makes it worth noticing\\n\\n## Godin Frameworks\\n\\n**Purple Cow**: \\\"What would make someone tell a friend about this?\\\"\\n**Category Positioning**: \\\"Are you creating new category or competing in existing?\\\"\\n\\n## Key Probes\\n- If too vague: What SPECIFICALLY do you do?\\n- If copying competitors: What's YOUR angle vs [competitor]?\\n- If multiple ideas: Pick ONE for this page\\n- If stuck: What problem frustrated YOU personally?\\n\\n## Red Flags\\n- \\\"I want to help people [generic]\\\" → need mechanism\\n- \\\"I'm building an app\\\" → what does it DO?\\n- Buzzword heavy → translate to plain language\\n- Industry name only → what makes yours unique?\\n\\n    \\n    <current_topic>idea</current_topic>\\n    \\n    <their_answer>Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.</their_answer>\\n    \\n    <qa_evaluation>\\n    Success: false\\n    Reasoning: The answer fails on multiple criteria:\\n\\n1. **Specific** - \\\"Podcast matchmaking service\\\" is too vague. What does matchmaking mean exactly? Matching podcasters with guests? Listeners with shows? Sponsors with creators? It could describe dozens of different services.\\n\\n2. **Actionable** - Can't write marketing copy from this. Need to know: Who are the actual users? What problem are they solving? What's the workflow?\\n\\n3. **Authentic** - \\\"Matchmaking service\\\" is generic business jargon. Needs plain language explanation of what actually happens.\\n\\n4. **Insightful** - Missing the \\\"why it matters\\\" entirely. What problem does this solve? Why would anyone need this?\\n\\n**Missing critical info:**\\n- Who it's for (podcasters? listeners? sponsors?)\\n- What specific problem it solves\\n- How it actually works\\n- What makes it different from existing solutions\\n\\nThis reads like an elevator pitch fragment, not a business idea. Needs: \\\"We help [WHO] do [WHAT] by [HOW], because [PROBLEM].\\\"\\n    </qa_evaluation>\\n    \\n    <chat_history>\\n        <chat-history>\\n  <message>\\n    human: \\\"Friend of the Pod is a podcast matchmaking service.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n  <message>\\n    assistant: \\\"Tell us about your business. More info → better outcomes.\\\"\\n  </message>\\n</chat-history>\\n    </chat_history>\\n    \\n    <task>\\n    Their answer isn't GREAT yet. Ask a specific follow-up that addresses \\n    the weakness identified in the QA evaluation.\\n    \\n    Be constructive and encouraging:\\n    1. Acknowledge what was good\\n    2. Identify the specific gap\\n    3. Ask targeted follow-up\\n    4. Provide examples\\n    \\n    Output JSON: {\\n      \\\"text\\\": \\\"Your clarifying question\\\",\\n      \\\"examples\\\": [\\\"Guiding example 1\\\", \\\"Example 2\\\"],\\n      \\\"conclusion\\\": \\\"Encouraging restatement\\\"\\n    }\\n    </task>\\n  \"}]}"
          },
          "queryString": [],
          "url": "https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages"
        },
        "response": {
          "bodySize": 1415,
          "content": {
            "mimeType": "application/json",
            "size": 1415,
            "text": "{\"model\":\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\",\"id\":\"msg_01AbgBrfJ3khcWLS6LxkPwZf\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015tv9WUZSNmpNjAZXMdQnqM\",\"name\":\"extract\",\"input\":{\"text\":\"I love that you have a clear name and you're thinking about *connection* — that's smart for podcasting. But \\\"matchmaking service\\\" could mean a few different things, and I want to make sure we nail what you actually do.\\n\\nHere's what I need: **Who are you matching with whom?** Are you connecting podcasters with guest experts? Listeners with shows they'd love? Sponsors with creators? Something else?\\n\\nOnce I know that, everything else clicks into place — the problem you're solving, who needs you, why they'd care.\",\"examples\":[\"We help podcast hosts find the right guest experts for their episodes\",\"We help listeners discover niche podcasts based on their interests\",\"We help sponsors find podcasters whose audiences match their target market\"],\"conclusion\":\"You're onto something real here — you just need to zoom in on the specific connection you're making. That one detail changes everything about how we talk about this.\"}}],\"stop_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1640,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":0,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":0},\"output_tokens\":255,\"service_tier\":\"standard\"}}"
